Class Summary
ByteTile  
OffscreenWindow this implements a window backed by a bitmap, but which doesn't touch the regular window system.
PlaytableServer info we have about a server that announced on the UDP hello service
ScreenScanner  
TileManager manages the tiles associated with a bitmap
UDPService This implements a simple "hello" service to allow peers on a network to discover one another.
VncAuxWindow  
VncDispatcher this is a generic dispatch window that allows a client to select one of the available services, and switch to it.
VncListener listen for connections on a socket, spawn a VNCTransmitter for each connection
VNCReceiver this implements a VNC-like client, but the actual protocols are strictly locally defined, unrelated to "real" vnc
VncRemote this is a generic "spectator" window that can be attached to any regular window It's not intended for use in production, but as a debugging vehicle
VNCService  
VNCTransmitter this implements a vnc-like host for screen sharing, but the actual messages and protols are not related to the standard vnc definitions
